      <p>Wonderful story. As a French-American, I grew up eating leeks vinaigrette quite a bit. What I love the most, though, is &#8220;fondue de poireaux&#8221;: leeks are cooked down and nearly caramelized. I can&#39;t get enough of them: they&#39;re sweet, silky, and melt in your mouth. A great pairing for salmon!</p>
