    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I find myself carting back lots of Fallot mustard on my Eurostar trips. As for the leeks, I stumbled over a recipe online (from William Sonoma French, I think), which calls for sauteing the leeks first, then poaching them until most of the liquid is gone, finally making a very thick vinaigrette with what remains. Not recommended for 40 people, but delicious nonetheless. The adapted recipe is here: <a href="http://lespetitpois.blogspot.com/2009/09/dijon-et-poireaux-vinaigrette.html" rel="nofollow ugc">http://lespetitpois.blogspot.com/2009/09/dijon-et-poireaux-vinaigrette.html</a>.</p>
    </div>

